args: Good morning, Cleo. Say, have you seen\nYaten anywhere? I can't find him.
No, he wasn't in his room this morning.\nBut he's such a hard worker, it wouldn't\nsurprise me if he got a jump on the day.
He's a real pro, all right. I can't wait\nto see the next thing he comes up with.
Er, I'm sorry for disturbing you both\nso early in the day, but there is a\nmatter that we need to discuss.
Of course. How can we help?
Well, I'm having second thoughts about\nwhether I should allow Yaten to plan\nour upcoming festival.
...I can't believe that Yaten is napping\nand slacking around town all day!
He seemed so serious about\nthe festival before.

The mayor appeared taken aback as well.
Still, there's only one way for us to
ascertain the truth, and that is by
asking Yaten directly.
He really IS napping! ...Also, he looks\nVERY comfortable on that bench.
No wonder the mayor was concerned.\nWe'd best go wake him up.
Hold on. It's possible he's just resting\nbecause he's been working since the\nsun first came up.
Let's wait a while longer and see\nwhat he does next.
I find your optimism almost charming,\nbut very well...
I fear Yaten shows no signs of moving\nfrom his comfortable bench.
We've given him enough of a chance.\nLet's march over there and—Oh!
I don't think we can conclude that until\nwe actually see him doing some WORK.\nLet us follow him and see what happens.
Of course, sir! One salted-meat sandwich\nand lentil soup, coming right up!
He appears to be getting lunch.
Well, he really wolfed that down.\nLet's see where he goes next!
I'm so happy to see you again, Yaten!
Can't get enough of the meat you got here.\nNow, what should I get today...?
How many stops does this make?
Umm, I think this is five?
This is no manner of work\nthat I am familiar with.
He's merely ambling around the town,\nstopping only to talk and eat!
SURELY he's going to start working soon.
Hold on. Is this not the park where we\nfirst saw him this morning?
*yawn* Guess I should hit the hay.
I cannot watch this idiocy a second longer!\nDon't stop me, {player_name}!
What do you think you are doing, Yaten?!
Wow, Cleo. You look pretty riled up.
You told us you were going to bring life\nback to this town with a festival!
Yet here you are sitting idly about!
You have spent the entire day napping,\ntalking, and cramming various foodstuffs\ninto your gaping maw! That is NOT work!
The mayor came to us to share his...\nconcerns about your work ethic.
So we decided to follow you and see if his\nworries were justified—which they most\nCLEARLY are, you slugabed!
Stalking someone isn't nice.\nAlso, I really WAS working.
No. Really. That's how I work.
I'm amazed you can afford the amount of\nmeals you eat if you consider that ＂work.＂
Excuse me there, but are you\nPrince {player_name}?
I was informed that you're footing the bill\nfor all of Yaten's meals, correct?
You there! Prince! I need you to pay off\nYaten's tab before I go broke!
Have you been eating for free all this\ntime by saying the prince will pay for\nyour meals?!
Now I understand why we never saw him\nhand over any money for his food.
You said you'd help however you could,\nright? Can't take that back now.
Anyway, I gotta get back to wor—
Stop goin' around causin' trouble!\nAlso, why the hell ain't you been\ncheckin' in with me?!
You don't need me to watch your\nevery move. I know you got this.
Yeah, but there are things *I* wanna talk\nto *you* about. Now get over here!
Hey! You're gonna yank my arm off!
She did make quite the entrance.\nStill, I think we can leave him to her.
